The paper deals with algorithms for searching for patterns in a text, which is a fundamental problem in computer science. The use of automata and the analysis of time and space complexity suggest that the paper belongs to the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The problem of searching for patterns in a text is also related to combinatorics (cs.DM), as it involves the study of permutations and order-isomorphisms. The use of Aho-Corasick algorithm and the extension to multiple patterns suggest that the paper may also belong to the category of computational complexity (cs.CC) and computational engineering, finance, and science (cs.CE). Finally, the analysis of average case complexity and optimality suggests that the paper may also belong to the category of computational geometry (cs.CG), which often deals with optimization problems.
